<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Document xmlns="http://www.suscopts.org/CopticReader">   <Section silent="true">              <Title>         <Language id="English">Prayer of Incense to the Son</Language>                     <Language id="Arabic">اوشية بخور للابن</Language>      </Title>                      <Role id="Priest" silent="true">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               The priest goes up to the altar placing his right foot first and takes the incense box into his hand, and inclining his head toward his fellow priests, says:            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               وفي اثناء ذلك يصعد الكاهن إلى المذبح برجله اليمنى ويأخذ درج البخور بيده ويطامن نحو الكهنة برأسه ويقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Eulogite.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Bless (you).            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               بارِكوا.            </Language>         </Text>                  <Comment>            <Language id="English">               If there is one priest present with him, he says:             </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               وإذا كان الحاضر عنده كاهن واحد يقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Eulog/con.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Bless (you).            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               بارِكْ.            </Language>         </Text>                  <Comment>            <Language id="English">               Inclining their heads toward the serving priest, the fellow priests answer:             </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ثم يطامنون هم أيضاً رؤوسهم ويجاوبونه قائلين:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Nyok eulog/con.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               May you bless.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               أنت بارِكْ.            </Language>         </Text>                  <Comment>            <Language id="English">               Then the priest turns to the altar and puts the incense box in its place, and laying his finger upon it, says:            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ثم يلتفت إلى المذبح ويضع درج البخور مكانه ويضع إصبعه عليه ويقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <InsertDocument path="include/KhenEfran"/>                  <Comment>            <Language id="English">               Having made the sign of the cross over the incense box, the priest puts the first spoonful of incense into the censer, saying:            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ثم يرشم الدرج ويضع البخور في المجمرة يداً أولى وهو يقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Fc~marwout n~je Vnou] Viwt pipantokratwr: a~m/n.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Blessed be God the Father, the Pantocrator. Amen.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مباركٌ الله الآب ضابطُ الكل. آمين.            </Language>         </Text>                  </Role>            <Role id="Deacon" silent="true">         <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Am/n.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Amen.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مين.            </Language>                  </Text>      </Role>            <Role id="Priest" silent="true">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               The priest, making the sign of the cross again, puts a second spoonful of incense into the censer, saying:            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ثم يرشم ويضع البخور يداً ثانية وهو يقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Fc~marwout n~je pefmonogen/c n~S/ri I/couc Pi,~rictoc Pen[oic: a~m/n.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Blessed be His only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ our Lord. Amen.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مباركٌ ابنُه الوحيدُ يسوعُ المسيح ربنا. آمين.            </Language>         </Text>      </Role>            <Role id="Deacon" silent="true">         <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Am/n.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Amen.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مين.            </Language>                  </Text>      </Role>             <Role id="Priest" silent="true">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               If there are fellow priests, then each one puts in a spoonful of incense a second time. Then, making the sign of the cross, the serving priest puts a third spoonful of incense into the censer, saying:            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               وإن كان معه شركاء فاليد الثانية لهم جميعاً واحداً بعد واحد، ثم يرشم رشماً ثالثاً ويضع البخور يداً ثالثةً ويقول:            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Fc~marwout n~je Pip~neuma eyouab m~parakl/ton.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Blessed be the Holy Spirit, the Paraclete.  (Amen.)            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مباركٌ الروحُ القدس المعزِّي. (آمين).            </Language>         </Text>      </Role>            <Role id="Deacon" silent="true">         <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Am/n.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Amen.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               مين.            </Language>                  </Text>      </Role>            <Role id="Priest" silent="true">         <Group>            <Season id="FirstProstration">               <Comment>                  <Language id="English">                     The priest puts four spoonfuls of incense into the censer. Then he puts the fifth spoonful in the pottery vessel, while praying the following inaudibly:                   </Language>                  <Language id="Arabic">                     يضع الكاهن أربع أيادى بخور فى المجمرة ثم يضع اليد الخامسة فى وعاء البخور الفخار وهو يصلى الآتى سراً:                  </Language>               </Comment>            </Season>                        <Season id="Other">               <Comment>                  <Language id="English">                     Then the priest puts two spoonfuls of incense into the censer, without making the sign of the cross, and says:                  </Language>                  <Language id="Arabic">                     ثم يضع يدي بخور أيضاً بلا رشم وهو يقول:                  </Language>               </Comment>                  </Season>         </Group>                  <InsertDocument path="include/GloryAndHonor"/>                  <Group>            <Season id="FirstProstration | ThirdProstration">               <InsertDocument path="prostration/include/SilentProcession"/>            </Season>         </Group>                  <Group>            <Season id="Vespers">               <InsertDocument path="include/ProcessionOfIncense_Vespers"/>            </Season>                        <Season id="Matins">               <InsertDocument path="include/ProcessionOfIncense_Matins"/>            </Season>         </Group>      </Role>            <Role id="Deacon" silent="true">         <Text>            <Language id="Coptic">               Proceuexacye u~per t/c yuciac /~mwn p~rocverontwn.            </Language>            <Language id="English">               Pray for our sacrifice and those who have brought it.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               صلوا من أجلِ ذبيحتنا، والذين قدموها.             </Language>                  </Text>      </Role>            <InsertDocument path="include/SilentPriestProcessionIntroduction1"/>            <Role id="Priest" silent="true">         <InsertDocument path="include/SilentPriestProcessionIntroIntro"/>         </Role>   </Section></Document>